17. An arrangement for providing electronic services comprising: 
a web server providing electronic transactions and services in response to requests of a computer connected to the Internet or to an Intranet network; 
a database for storing predetermined threshold values corresponding to different customers; 
a monitor for the response time of said transactions; and 
a processor for automatically modifying said transactions in response to said monitored response time reaching at least one predetermined threshold value.
